{
  "texts": [
    "For both reactions, there were four variables to optimize, including metrics for reaction time, reagent concentration, and temperature.",
    "After an initial sampling of 20 experimental conditions by LHS, the choice of reaction conditions was left to the TSEMO algorithm, optimizing the S N Ar within a total of 48 iterations and the N-benzylation reaction within a total of 58 iterations.",
    "Both optimizations resulted in the discovery of a dense Pareto front with approximately 30-50% of the total suggested conditions resulting in nondominated solutions.",
    "Since then, multiple reports have demonstrated the ability of TSEMO to optimize multiobjective optimizations for the synthesis of organic molecules (see examples in Table 2, entries 3-5 and 7-9).",
    "A particularly noteworthy development is the application of TSEMO for the optimization of synthetic routes composed of two and more successive reaction steps or telescoped reactions [83][84][85]."
  ]
}